ddress\tSystem delivered (3-7 days)\t30 min\tOnline retailer 6\tGather Tools (DIY Path)\tAccess to tools or purchase\tAssembled toolkit: 2 adjustable wrenches, Teflon tape, pipe cutter, bucket, towels\t1 hour\tHardware store: ~ 50−80 if buying Installation Day (DIY Path) Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tTime\tCritical Notes 7\tShut Off Main Water\tTurn valve clockwise until fully closed\tNo water flow from any faucet\t2 min\tNotify household members first 8\tDrain System\tOpen lowest faucet in home (basement sink/outdoor spigot)\tWater stops draining after 5-10 minutes\t10 min\tThis prevents flooding during installation 9\tCut Into Main Line\tMark cut locations 18\" apart on cold water line after meter\tTwo clean cuts, remove 18\" section of pipe\t20 min\tUse pipe cutter, not saw (cleaner cut) 10\tInstall Mounting Bracket\tUse included bracket, drill into wall stud or concrete\tFilter system bracket securely mounted at waist height\t15 min\tEnsure level installation for proper function 11\tConnect Inlet\tApply 12-15 wraps Teflon tape to threads, hand-tighten, then wrench-tighten\tInlet connected to incoming water line (from street), no leaks\t15 min\tTape direction: clockwise when looking at threads 12\tConnect Outlet\tSame Teflon tape process\tOutlet connected to house distribution line, no leaks\t15 min\tDouble-check inlet/outlet orientation (arrows on housing) 13\tInstall Pressure Gauges\tScrew into gauge ports (if included)\tGauges installed, readable position\t10 min\tOptional but recommended for monitoring 14\tTurn Water Back On SLOWLY\tOpen main valve 1/4 turn, wait 30 seconds, continue gradually\tWater flowing, check all connections for leaks\t5 min\tSlow opening prevents pressure surge 15\tFlush System\tRun cold water taps for 5-10 minutes\tClear water, no black carbon particles (initial flush)\t10 min\tNormal to see carbon fines initially 16\tCheck for Leaks\tInspect all connections, feel for moisture\tAll connections dry, no drips\t10 min\tT